data.name: textBoxCHH.ToolTip
data.value: Upper bound on random center hold time. Center hold time is the time between when the cursor enters the center target and the outer target appears. Set equal to Center Hold Low for non-random hold time.

data.name: textBoxCHL.ToolTip
data.value: Lower bound on random center hold time. Center hold time is the time between when the cursor enters the center target and the outer target appears. Set equal to Center Hold High for non-random hold time.

data.name: textBoxRWLowerTgtBound.ToolTip
data.value: Lower (closest to monkey) workspace boundry. Use negative values to set the to the below the origin. Defines the workspace in which targets can be presented in cartesian coordinates (cm) about the origin.

data.name: textBoxRWUpperTgtBound.ToolTip
data.value: Upper (away from monkey) workspace boundry. Use negative values to set the to the below the origin. Defines the workspace in which targets can be presented in cartesian coordinates (cm) about the origin.

data.name: textBoxRWTgtTol.ToolTip
data.value: Distance (in cm) from the displayed target the cursor must be to be counted as in the target. Use negative values to make the target smaller than displayed, positive ones to make the target larger than displayed.

data.name: label42.ToolTip
